Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.34,0:00:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two of them twenty years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.35,0:00:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And one fifteen years ago, became victims of the serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.52,0:00:09.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was then that that the criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.02,0:00:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran down Superintendent Morimura with his car and killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.52,0:00:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Superintendent Matsumoto in turn followed him,\Nand ended up with a scar over his left eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.65,0:00:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the cases twenty years ago, their respective statutes have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.03,0:00:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for the case from 15 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.70,0:00:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are still three days until the time runs out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.99,0:00:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two clues that connect the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.66,0:00:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first: A scar on the culprit's back\Ncourtesy of Superintendent Matsumoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.17,0:00:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other: Whistling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.50,0:00:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A song that was popular twenty years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.67,0:00:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was always whistling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.84,0:00:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}As Detective Takagi and the others carried out their investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.99,0:00:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}A criminologist by the name of Hiramune Douji-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.10,0:00:48.22,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\fs14\b}Hiramune Douji (41)\NCriminal Psychologist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.81,0:00:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Appeared on TV and repeatedly provoked the\Ncriminal as he had in magazines before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.10,0:00:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.69,0:00:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We happened to pass a strange man near the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.40,0:01:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a man who was whistling and wearing an off-season long coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.28,0:01:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.37,0:01:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He actually came here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.12,0:01:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.85,0:01:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is eternal, labyrinths are mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.00,0:01:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saturday nights are for mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.26,0:01:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something is different about Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.28,0:01:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will it be a straight line to arrest the culprit!?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.39,0:01:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.01,0:01:23.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.88,0:01:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.83,0:03:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously, Conan-kun!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.29,0:03:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying that, at that apartment building...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.79,0:03:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly likely that the serial killer appeared!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.87,0:03:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.57,0:03:29.18,title001,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.3\fad(250,0)}Hiramune
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That criminal psychologist, Hiramune-san,\Njust ridiculed the serial killer on TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.42,0:03:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he may have come to his apartment!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.01,0:03:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, I'm going to check out his room!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.47,0:03:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.89,0:03:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.30,0:03:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chiba-kun, ready the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.18,0:03:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.77,0:03:38.57,title002,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.3}Hiramune
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.06,0:03:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.36,0:03:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unlocked...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:03:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.16,0:03:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.58,0:04:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune-sa—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.17,0:04:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.26,0:04:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.35,0:04:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.47,0:04:19.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a {\c&H4F4FF3&}Z{\1c}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.77,0:04:24.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is the criminal psychologist, Hiramune Douji-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.69,0:04:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Age 41.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.15,0:04:28.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder weapon was a fruit knife from the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging by the stun-gun markings on his neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as the alphabet letter carved into his back...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.66,0:04:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, this was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.20,0:04:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The work of the serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.33,0:04:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this time, the letter is a {\c&H4F4FF3&}Z{\1c}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.29,0:04:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I completely expected an {\c&HF6EA52&}N{\1c} this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.67,0:04:51.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging by the investigation reports...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.59,0:04:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The letters carved on the previous victims were...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.84,0:04:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\c&H58FD50&}E {\c&H40DAFF&}S {\c&HAB4CFC&}W {\1c}— in that order.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.89,0:05:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should it have been an {\c&HF6EA52&}N{\1c} this time, we\Nwould have east/west and south/north.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.69,0:05:12.54,title003,,0,0,0,,Touzai (East/West)\h\h\h\h\h\N\NNanboku (South/North)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.69,0:05:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.56,0:05:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's Touzai Nanboku...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.40,0:05:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}That's {\c&H58FD50&}East, {\c&HAB4CFC&}West, {\c&H40DAFF&}South, {\c&HF6EA52&}North{\1c}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.07,0:05:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\c&H58FD50&}E {\c&HAB4CFC&}W {\c&H40DAFF&}S {\c&HF6EA52&}N{\1c}, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.86,0:05:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we can be sure it wasn't a copycat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:21.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is, since the culprit cutting letters into the\Nbodies of his victims was never made public.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.37,0:05:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems Conan-kun's friends passed by the\Nman as he was whistling near the entrance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.92,0:05:29.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, with only knowing this much...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.88,0:05:32.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you heard your friends mention a man that was whistling...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You remembered him ridiculing the culprit on TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.01,0:05:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then thought Hiramune-san might be in danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.72,0:05:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which caused you to rush over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.56,0:05:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're as attentive as a police detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.56,0:05:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.15,0:05:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.15,0:05:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it really that provoking?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.36,0:05:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The suspect is likely trembling in bed,\Nwaiting for the deadline to pass."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.78,0:05:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In the event that isn't the case, come kill me."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.87,0:06:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a challenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.62,0:06:02.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.87,0:06:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune-san was known for this style\Nof writing in newspapers and weeklies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.04,0:06:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Hiramune-san immediately left the TV studio\Nafter his appearance at 4:00, and hurried home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.88,0:06:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, he said he was going to meet an acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.39,0:06:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's very likely that this acquaintance is the suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:21.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.89,0:06:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That certain someone is related to a copy machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.18,0:06:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, underneath Hiramune-san's left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.27,0:06:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The {\1c&HA0A2A3&}Ctrl {\1c}and {\1c&HA0A2A3&}C {\1c}keys are stained with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.65,0:06:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you press those two keys together, don't you get "copy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.11,0:06:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.87,0:06:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could have been left deliberately by the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.16,0:06:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, there's no blood on his left hand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.46,0:06:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is there just blood on his right hand that's grasping the mouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.13,0:06:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.26,0:06:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stained the keyboard with his bloody right hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.59,0:06:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then specially covered it with his left hand, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.76,0:07:04.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the suspect had planned this, would he have done that as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.06,0:07:05.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.64,0:07:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would focus on making it more noticeable, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.35,0:07:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since his left hand wasn't covered in blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.81,0:07:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know he didn't end up staining the keys by chance while typing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.57,0:07:15.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that means he used his left hand to cover it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.44,0:07:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Simply because he didn't want the suspect to notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.65,0:07:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, this—which was left by\NHiramune-san just as he was dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.45,0:07:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amounts to a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.25,0:07:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There also seems to be a copy machine in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.29,0:07:33.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I inspected it earlier, but I didn't find anything out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.09,0:07:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be a copy band?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.76,0:07:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspect was always whistling a song that\Nwas popular some twenty years ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.89,0:07:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that mean he could know people from a copy band?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.72,0:07:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many such bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.56,0:07:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Superintendent Matsumoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.68,0:07:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Superintendent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.85,0:07:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means it could be a song that's popular all over the world, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.98,0:07:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, as for the serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.48,0:07:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This melody holds some sort of deeper meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.86,0:08:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deeper meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.53,0:08:02.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Immediately after that incident twenty years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.82,0:08:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morimura was questioning drivers of suspicious\Ncars that frequented the area of the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.87,0:08:11.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was during the questioning that he was struck\Nby a car and killed in the line of duty, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.04,0:08:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.88,0:08:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Morimura approached the car, he noticed that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.80,0:08:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspect was whistling at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.76,0:08:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While tears poured down his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.55,0:08:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tears?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.22,0:08:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satou, Chiba — inquire around the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.35,0:08:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.22,0:08:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiratori, look into everyone related to Hiramune-san\Nagain, but with the clue of the copy machine in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was my intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.65,0:08:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, just in case, visit the relatives of the previous three victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.32,0:08:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See if they have any connection at all to Hiramune-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.99,0:08:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.03,0:08:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.66,0:08:44.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.16,0:08:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he's enthusiastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.04,0:08:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like my medicine has been more than effective, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.92,0:08:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only three days remain before the\Nstatute on the murder case is reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.38,0:09:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if the criminal has committed a new offense,\Nthe statute will last another fifteen years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.97,0:09:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.22,0:09:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Code of Criminal Procedure was amended...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The statute of limitations on murder cases\Nwas extended to twenty-five years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.10,0:09:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So long as I can catch the serial killer\Nwithin the next twenty-five years...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satou-san and I can go to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.07,0:09:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.03,0:09:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.16,0:09:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would explain why you were more enthusiastic than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.66,0:09:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your motives are impure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hot spring, that's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.87,0:09:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should take us with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.46,0:09:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you all doing in my car!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the one who let us in back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.89,0:09:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You asked us, "Where do you want to go?" in the parking lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.60,0:09:50.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And opened the door without saying anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't seem like you were really paying attention, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.77,0:10:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about the hot sprin—I mean, I had the case in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.69,0:10:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.44,0:10:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you permit us to stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.99,0:10:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or will we be dropped off?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.70,0:10:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I'll be dropping you off!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.28,0:10:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Ayumi-chan and Haibara-san saw the culprit, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.04,0:10:16.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.12,0:10:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to the homes of the relatives of the\Nvictims fifteen and twenty years ago right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.34,0:10:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The family of the victims were all considered suspects as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.05,0:10:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or so, that's what they said on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.26,0:10:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.76,0:10:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if this continues for another twenty-five years...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.72,0:10:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And assuming Detective Satou is still waiting for you\Nas a 50 year-old woman with wrinkles on her face...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.56,0:10:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you can try to do it all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.07,0:10:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So hollow...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.94,0:10:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will be fine if you do it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.57,0:10:45.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's still really beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.99,0:10:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's worth it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.66,0:10:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.79,0:10:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only Conan-kun is conning with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.08,0:10:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rest of you need to wait patiently in the car, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.67,0:11:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.75,0:11:04.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.76,0:11:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one we're here to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.67,0:11:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the widow of the doctor that was murdered\Ntwenty years ago, Boukawa Tsuguharu-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.97,0:11:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.10,0:11:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boukawa-san was the clinic head of a large hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.10,0:11:21.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because his wife, Maiko-san, inherited a large fortune with his death...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.31,0:11:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She became suspect and was called in for a number of line-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.98,0:11:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we had no proof, and since there was no\Nconnection to the second victim, Mugita-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.78,0:11:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She remained only a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.83,0:11:38.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.05,0:11:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}This is the criminal psychologist that seems\Nto always be on TV—Hiramune-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.41,0:11:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.05,0:11:46.42,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\fs14\blur2}Boukawa Maiko (62)\NWife of Boukawa Tsuguharu
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.67,0:11:50.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was found murdered in his apartment earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.55,0:11:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one responsible is most likely the very same\Nperson that killed your husband twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.68,0:11:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, that's upsetting...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.56,0:12:04.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, we've come to ask if your husband had\Nany sort of connection with Hiramune-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.40,0:12:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.65,0:12:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just how old was this Hiramune-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.86,0:12:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was 41 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.86,0:12:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when my husband was killed twenty\Nyears ago, he would have only been 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.78,0:12:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband was 50 years old when he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.95,0:12:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine there's any link between them...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.87,0:12:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.58,0:12:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure he never met anyone in secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.67,0:12:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this child?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.96,0:12:31.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm here to observe how policemen work for my social studies class!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.97,0:12:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.85,0:12:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it is true that he would often go out for\Ndrinks with someone on Saturday nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.73,0:12:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea who that was!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.06,0:12:43.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.56,0:12:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But once, when he returned home especially drunk, he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.57,0:12:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Damn! Wouldn't stop with the 'crybaby,\Ncrybaby,' making me out to be an idiot!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.61,0:12:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said something along those lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.12,0:13:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably an old friend my husband knew from his childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.16,0:13:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told all of this to the police twenty years ago, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.46,0:13:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The relative we're visiting next is for\Nthe second victim twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.63,0:13:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murdered just two days after Boukawa-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll see the younger brother of that associate professor\Nof science and engineering, Mugita Atsunori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.76,0:13:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As beneficiary in his brother's sizable life insurance\Npolicy, he was also considered a suspect, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.35,0:13:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like with the wife of the first victim,\Nthere was no connection between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.27,0:13:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the third victim, Nabei-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.86,0:13:33.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, there was no connection found there either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.62,0:13:42.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a criminal psychologist named Hiramune Douji-san, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.48,0:13:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}No matter how many talk shows the guy has been on...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.51,0:13:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}It doesn't change the fact that I dislike TV, you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.46,0:13:49.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\blur2\fad(250,0)}Mugita Hidekuni (56)\NYounger Brother Of Mugita Atsunori
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.71,0:13:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Hiramune-san has been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.67,0:13:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're confident it was the same one who\Nmurdered your brother, Atsunori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.09,0:13:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.47,0:14:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.68,0:14:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the statute on his case expired five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.02,0:14:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I decided to forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.65,0:14:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.65,0:14:12.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible your brother and Hiramune-san knew one another?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.36,0:14:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.49,0:14:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.95,0:14:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saturday nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.58,0:14:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did your brother happen to meet with anyone on Saturday nights?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would often venture out on Saturday\Nnights and not return until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother's wife, who died the\Nyear before last, told me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.88,0:14:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was worried he was using Saturday nights for an affair,\Nand would always call his pager to keep tabs on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.93,0:14:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems my brother would grow angry as he called back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.69,0:14:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm going to the Doctor's now!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.19,0:14:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Quit nagging!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.27,0:14:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.86,0:14:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that doctor be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.90,0:14:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first victim in the case, Doctor Boukawa!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.99,0:14:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:15:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told the police about it twenty years\Nago, and it seems they looked into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.95,0:15:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently my brother's name wasn't on his patient list, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.67,0:15:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That does seem to be the case, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.59,0:15:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.55,0:15:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you come across something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.76,0:15:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you, Ayumi-chan and Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.56,0:15:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did either seem similar to the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.06,0:15:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't notice any similarities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.36,0:15:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I don't think it was the old lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.48,0:15:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if they had been wearing a wig and synthetic\Nfacial hair when we passed by them earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.53,0:15:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible our impression could change, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.66,0:15:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.08,0:15:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are we headed next?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.87,0:15:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, the last one is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.12,0:15:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Related to the murder case that occurred\Nfive years after the cases twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.96,0:15:56.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be meeting Eika-san, who is the son\Nof the murdered lawyer, Nabei Susumu.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiki-san was just 10 years old at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.31,0:16:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was sleeping in his room and was awoken by his father's moaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.65,0:16:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Between when the culprit left and his\Nmother returned home from shopping...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.57,0:16:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was too scared to even leave his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.07,0:16:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His mother went into shock after seeing her\Nhusband's body, and ended up bedridden...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.87,0:16:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She is still hospitalized to this day, and\NEiki-san continues to live alone in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.25,0:16:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enough is enough, Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have I not discussed this case with the police enough!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.18,0:16:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}With this deadline coming up...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.68,0:16:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}The news people are all over me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.30,0:16:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'm tired of this shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.93,0:16:43.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\fad(210,0)}Nabei Eiki (25)\NSon of Nabei Susumu
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.97,0:16:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what if this criminal that killed my father got someone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.60,0:16:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How does that concern me!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.94,0:16:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.52,0:16:55.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just want to know if your father was\Nacquainted with this man, Hiramune-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.02,0:16:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.90,0:16:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.11,0:16:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.66,0:17:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he wasn't always like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.08,0:17:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.12,0:17:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.12,0:17:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the inspector, when the boy\Nwas questioned about the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.62,0:17:17.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He claimed that, before the murder, his\Nfather had said something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.71,0:17:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems every time he remembered something, he\Nwould come to the police to report it immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.47,0:17:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.30,0:17:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He usually slept until noon on Sundays, and it seems\Nhe was mumbling something after waking up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.97,0:17:33.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Had some parents run over last night as well, too bad."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.31,0:17:33.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.52,0:17:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's parents were probably run over by a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.82,0:17:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.94,0:17:41.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because he was a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.11,0:17:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably decided to defend the ones\Nresponsible or the victims involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.95,0:17:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.91,0:17:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is that considered strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.41,0:17:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder victim, Nabei-san, specialized in corporate cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.50,0:17:55.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears he never took on a traffic case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.75,0:17:57.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.13,0:18:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Eiki-san found it strange and didn't\Nunderstand it either, so he reported it to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.76,0:18:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs15\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HC5A999&}nakimushi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.76,0:18:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HC5A999&}Crybaby...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs15\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HABD3D2&}isha ni itte n da
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HABD3D2&}Going to the Doctor's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.43,0:18:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs15\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HE59BB9&}oya haneru
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.43,0:18:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And {\1c&HE59BB9&}parents {\1c}being {\1c&HE59BB9&}run over, {\1c}huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.85,0:18:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.69,0:18:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.73,0:18:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The connection between the four victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.57,0:18:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.20,0:18:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The connection between the four serial murder victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.33,0:18:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really just mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.29,0:18:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune-san said it when he was on the talk show, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.58,0:18:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when he said, "He'll keep disposing of his\Nsafe tiles, just waiting for this round to end."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.88,0:18:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all mahjong terminology, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.22,0:18:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune-san must have truly liked mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That may be true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.81,0:18:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the other three?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.47,0:18:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first victim that was killed, the doctor, Boukawa-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.06,0:18:59.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came home drunk one Saturday night...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.55,0:19:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HC5A999&\fad(250,250)}nakimushi nakimushi tte baka ni shi ya gatte
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.81,0:19:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And apparently said, "Wouldn't stop with the\N'crybaby, crybaby,' making me out to be an idiot"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.15,0:19:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the associate professor of\Nscience and engineering, Mugita-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.82,0:19:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also on Saturday nights, his wife would call\Nhis pager, and when he called back...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.70,0:19:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HABD3D2&\fad(250,0)}ima isha ni itte n da jama sun na
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.70,0:19:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm going to the Doctor's now, stop nagging," he said angrily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.79,0:19:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lawyer who was killed five years\Nlater, Nabei-san, got up one Sunday...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.17,0:19:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the first thing he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HE59BB9&\fad(250,0)}yuube mo oya ga hane rare te taihen datta
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was something like,"Had some parents run\Nover last night as well, too bad," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.96,0:19:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The {\1c&HC5A999&}crybaby {\1c}Boukawa-san mentioned was actually\Nmisheard for what's known as {\1c&HC5A999&}opening doors {\1c}in mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.30,0:19:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he want to cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.18,0:19:34.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't mahjong just a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.27,0:19:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's when you try to hurry and win early...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.06,0:19:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By collecting tiles discarded by other\Nplayers, to form groups of 3's and 4's.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.48,0:19:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's {\1c&HC5A999&}opening doors{\1c}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.48,0:19:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HC5A999&\fad(250,0)}naku
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.19,0:19:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an7\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HE59BB9&\fad(250,250)}oya ga hane rare te haihen datta
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.19,0:19:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Had some parents run over last night as well, too bad" means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an7\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HCBCECC&\fad(250,250)}oya {\1c&H69FEF8&}ni {\1c&HCBCECC&}hane rare te haihen datta
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could have been, "{\1c&HCBCECC&}Had {\1c&HE59BB9&\} oya {\1c&H69FEF8&}ni {\1c&HCBCECC&}run over last night as well, too bad."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.66,0:19:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His son Eiki-san could have misheard that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.58,0:20:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The {\1c&HE59BB9&}parent {\1c}in mahjong refers to {\1c&HE59BB9&}the dealer{\1c},\Nwho can capitalize for extra points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.58,0:20:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an7\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HE59BB9&\fad(250,250)}\h\hoya
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.50,0:20:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an9\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HE59BB9&\fad(250,250)}oya yaku
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.17,0:20:05.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an7\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HE59BB9&\fad(250,250)}\h\hhane rareru
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.17,0:20:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To personally be {\1c&HE59BB9&}run over {\1c}is to be overtaken by\Nsomeone who has more points, thereby losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.01,0:20:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.96,0:20:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What he really meant was, "{\1c&HE59BB9&}Had the dealer\Nrun me over last night as well, too bad.{\1c}"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.50,0:20:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HABD3D2&\fad(250,250)}ima isha ni itte n
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.89,0:20:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about Mugita-san saying, "I'm going to the Doctor's now"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.64,0:20:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.35,0:20:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HB5BBB7&\fad(250,0)}ima {\1c\1c&HABD3D2&}ishaniten {\1c&HB5BBB7&}da
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.35,0:20:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"{\1c&HABD3D2&}I'm listening to the tiles now, stop nagging,{\1c}" or...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.35,0:20:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.86,0:20:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.69,0:20:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does sound like "going to the Doctor's."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what does that mean, "{\1c&HABD3D2&}listening to the tiles{\1c}"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.66,0:20:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you're just one tile away from a\Nwin, it's called "{\1c\1c&HABD3D2&}listening to the tiles{\1c}."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.08,0:20:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an8\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&HABD3D2&\fad(250,0)}iishanten
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.08,0:20:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"One more" tile is what you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.08,0:20:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he angrily said, "{\1c&HABD3D2&}I'm listening to the tiles, stop nagging.{\1c}"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.88,0:20:46.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an7\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&H957963&\fad(340,0)}\h\hnaku
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an7\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&H704459&\fad(340,0)}\h\hhane rareru
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fs14\fngungsuh\an7\be35\bord2\xbord20\ybord5\1c&H507F81&\fad(340,0)}\h\hiishanten
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since everything they said involved mahjong terminology,\Nit shouldn't be surprising that non-players misheard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.97,0:20:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.55,0:21:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who heard these statements were\NBoukawa-san and Mugita-san's wives...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.18,0:21:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as Nabei-san's son, Eiki-san, who was still a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.77,0:21:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the suspect said when Eiki-san was\Na child was also related to mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.48,0:21:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the suspect said?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.99,0:21:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the suspect killed his father and was\Non his way out, Eiki-san apparently heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.58,0:21:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Don't think I'm cruel."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.20,0:21:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm having you pay your dues."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.20,0:21:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Because you had to talk like that, I had to ready my hand."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.25,0:21:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And as a result, I ended up with this long scar from the cops."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.17,0:21:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.67,0:21:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Paying your dues and readying your hand are both part of mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.01,0:21:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.43,0:21:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.39,0:21:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.10,0:21:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The probability of those four meeting for\Nmahjong on Saturday nights is high.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.73,0:21:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now is the time to narrow our search to the mahjong parlors...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.73,0:21:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That those four could have accessed easily from their homes and jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.74,0:21:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to mahjong parlors, even complete strangers\Nwill play together, with no mind for differences in age.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.29,0:22:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.79,0:22:04.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Boys...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.62,0:22:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.04,0:22:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For you all, is the time all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.09,0:22:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already 9:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.97,0:22:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.38,0:22:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We told our moms we would be staying at the Professor's tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.64,0:22:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"No problem."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.55,0:22:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.18,0:22:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.19,0:22:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.98,0:22:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just wait, Whistling Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.89,0:24:01.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's our man on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.56,0:24:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take absolute caution!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.50,0:24:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to hostages, I guess it'll just be me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.38,0:22:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll uncover your true face without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.32,0:24:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.72,0:24:34.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.45,0:24:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Why is it called a mouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.40,0:24:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}You'll know next week!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.96,0:24:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Genta's talking strangely...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.40,0:24:39.42,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Look forward to the next episode
